Keep something in mind though: just because you and all your buddies do something doesn't make it a majority. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=finiel@graffeswizardcompilation>Finiel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 2:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lost Dungeons of Norrath Interview</span><hr size=1> I am looking forward to this. I'm not a big fan of instancing, but it may be a necessary evil. When players are left to their own devices, they tend to either camp a room in a dungeon, or avoid the dungeon completely. Gathering a group of people who are interested in crawling can be difficult (until you get a regular group together) because you need to go to less popular dungeons to crawl, but people don't want to hang out in those dungeons because they can't get pick-up groups there.<br>
<br>
Sometimes these multiplayer games remind me of the Monty Python skit &quot;Bicycle repair man&quot; where everyone is Superman. Since everybody is an adventurer, the adventure areas can get crowded.<br>
<br>
Most people are not in any danger of using up the  &quot;end game&quot; content that there is, adding more of that would be foolish. (2% is certainly not a major underestimation of the players who are in elementals+.)<br>
<br>
A series of dungeons linked by quests which help to tie the storyline of Norrath together. Each dungeon is designed to both challenge and reward the specific group that enters it, and should be completed in 45 to 90 minutes. The promise sounds good. We will have to see how much of that it lives up to, but I am glad to see the shift in focus from increasing the top level game.<br>
<br>
The addition of breakable objects and the idea of catering each dungeon to the group on the mission makes me think they could make Al'Kabor spells useful. Five carefully placed objects that must be damaged simultaneously could do it.<br>
The updated www.lostdungeonsofnorrath.com site has some screenshots and some more teaser information up now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimstafftheurgist>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 8231<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 4:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lost Dungeons of Norrath Interview</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Five carefully placed objects that must be damaged simultaneously could do it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
