<br>
Most people do 'raid'.  But I think the problem is you're defining raid as something completely different.<br>
<br>
I can't think of a single guild that doesn't want to raid, in some manner.  Granted, some of them don't do it often, but I think every guild does it.  Some guilds can only manage a group, some unfortunately can't even do that. BUT ALL OF THEM RAID.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>.raid., a hostile or predatory incursion : a surprise attack by a small force; a brief foray outside one's usual sphere : a daring operation against a competitor</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
Now, I will fully admit that LDoN could qualify in some aspect as raiding, but IMO the information we have makes it sound like it will be able to be completed by a standard XP group (i.e. very little challenge).<br>
<br>
A *NORMAL* xp group should never be able to get gear equivelent to gear that rivals what you would have earned by taking 30 well equipped people into a dangerous situation.<br>
<br>
Now, if the dungeons scale difficulty correctly, and you can take a Time equipped group in and get some loot that they would actually want to keep, then LDoN works perfectly.  However, if you can bring a Kunark equipped group in and get Elemental level loot, the entire game is going to suffer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elidaarruneweaver>Elidaar Runeweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 7:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Befallen</span><hr size=1> &gt;I thought Befallen was Tashkiz'Hiz. Hmm.<br>
<br>
Befallen was originally an outpost in the Commonlands for the Paladins of Marr; their largest fortress to control the onslaught of the Deathfist on Freeport.  It was destroyed in one night by an evil force contained within a wandering lunatic by the name of Gynok Moltor (the named mummy in the Paw of Opolla quest). <br>
