<br>
If that team gets too big your individual contribution tends to get lost.  If the amount of time it takes to accomplish what you're trying to do is too long then it gets boring after awhile.  60-90 minutes is about equal to my &quot;fun&quot; attention span time.  When I go over that it usually starts to get really monotonous.  <br>
<br>
SOE seems to be really trying to make EQ into a legitimately good game rather than a timesink for people with social problems.  I'm all for it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jjakajuan>JJakaJuan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 9:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> TOFS</span><hr size=1> If the dungeons are as fun as TOFS I would consider playing again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://jjakajuan.homestead.com/files/spike.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elharinalokhem>Elharina Lokhem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 367<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/03 9:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TOFS</span><hr size=1> I really can't wait for this expansion. Having left a raiding guild a little before they hit the elemental planes due to time constraints and a general boredom with the whole raiding scene I ended up joining a small guild of good friends who like tearing around Norrath getting ourselves in trouble and having fun. Suddenly I remembered why I actualyl started playing this game again. It wasn't to kill gods (hell there wasn't even a god up until after I bought EQ) it was to hang around with mates and get in trouble in some deep horrible pit surrounded by nasty critters who wanted a piece of me. <br>
